## Naming

Names are the primary documentation for AI agents and future maintainers.

| What | Convention | Why |
|---|---|---|
| Functions | `verb + noun` — `fetchAlerts`, `dismissAlert` | Reads as an action |
| Booleans | `is/has/can/should` prefix | Reads as a yes/no question |
| Event handlers | `handle` prefix — `handleDismiss` | Distinguishes internal handler from the prop |
| Callback props | `on` prefix — `onDismiss` | Mirrors native DOM events |
| Module-level constants | `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` | Signals "fixed and intentional" |
| Async functions | Suffix with the intent, not the mechanism — `loadAlerts`, not `fetchAlertsAsync` | The `async` keyword already marks it async |

